==English==

===Etymology===
Latin ''[[alleviare]]'' 'lighten'.

===Pronunciation===
*[[w:International Phonetic Alphabet|IPA]]:/əlivieɪt/

===Verb===
{{en-verb}}

# Of pain or difficulty, to make less severe.
#:*Alcohol is often a cheap tool to '''alleviate''' the stress of a hard day.

